0.title: Web in a Day
0.description: Web in a Day is the first in a series of tutorials to learn how to create modern websites using Jekyll. This Kickstarter focus on the basics of Jekyll and the J1 Template which all people needs to know for a successful way to a modern static website using Jekyll and J1 Template

1.title: Roundtrip
1.description: This page show some of quite useful features of J1 Template to manage your image-based content using lightboxes, carousels (slider) and galleries. The image module offers complex functionality based on powerful OpenSource libraries like Justified Gallery for high-end, masonry styled preview maps. A carousel app, using the jQuery plugin Owl Carousel as a base, let you present your images as slide shows. Lightboxes like LightGallery or Lightbox V2 support your web for full image views of your picture or video content. Have a look, a quick tour what J1 can do for image data.

2.title: Roundtrip
2.description: Playing video on web pages seems not that special since you can already watch videos on web pages through plugins like Flash Player, Quicktime or Silverlight. A new standard goes to HTML5 Video, a pure HTML way to show video on the web; instead of the previous de facto standard of using proprietary software.

6.title: Roundtrip
6.description: J1 Template support popular icons font sets out-of-the-box. The icon sets MDI and FA are very good in design and have a rich set of different icons for many categories used for the Web. Iconify icons is not a locally stored icon-set like MDI or FA. All icons are loaded over the Internet using the so-called Unified OpenSource Icon Framework.

7.title: Roundtrip
7.description: J1 Template implements some incubating Ruby-based extensions for Asciidoctor. Most extensions are based on the examples given with the Asciidoctor Extensions Lab. All implemented Asciidoctor Extensions can be found in this article. A set of useful extensions to the Markup language Asciidoc are made especially for documents of the Jekyll content type pages, but can be used for post or collections as well.

8.title: Roundtrip
8.description: Bootstrap modals are used to add dialogues to your web pages for user notifications. To highlight important information to your visitor's. Modals are positioned over everything else in the document so that messages get the users attention.

9.title: Roundtrip
9.description: Creating a design for responsive tables is challenging. The approach used by J1 Template is based on pure CSS on top of the classic Bootstrap styles for simplicity and portability to be viewed best on all devices and browsers.

10.title: Roundtrip
10.description: The themes feature for J1 is in an experimental state for the template system. Anyway, it makes sense to present what is possible using different versions of Bootstrap's CSS styles for a website.

11.title: Lunr
11.description: Learn the search query language used by Lunr. The DSL used by Lunr is quite close to Solr to support a powerful search experience for better result. Using search expressions with wildcards, conditions like and|or and fuzzy search algorithms are supported.

12.title: Floating Action Menu
12.description: A floating action button (FAB) represents the primary action/s of a page. Multiple actions can be configured as a FAM, the floating action menu. See FAM buttons and menus in action

19.title: Framer
19.description: Test page for J1 module framer. Framer enables the automatic resizing of the height and width of both same and cross domain iFrames to fit their contained content. It provides a range of features to address the most common issues with using HTML iFrames.

21.title: Gallery Previewer
21.description: To create modern image and video galleries, J1 Template implements the jQuery plugin JustifiedGallery. The module is a great tool to create responsive, infinite, and high quality justified image galleries. See Justified Gallery in action - and for sure all that you see is even responsive. Change the e.g. the size of your current browser window, by width or height. From the config menu, some basic features of Justified Gallery can be changed online. See what will happen!

22.title: MDI Icon Previewer
22.description: Previewer for Material Design Icons (MDI) for J1 Template. Material Design Icons is a growing icon collection allows designers and developers targeting various platforms to download icons in the format, color and size they need for any project.

23.title: J1 Template
23.description: A good user experience browsing a Web is one of the most important features a site has to offer as a must. Beside excellent content. Presenting content at it’s best on all devices, for all window sizes makes an excellent Web brilliant. J1 Template support your Web for full responsiveness, for the best user experience on all modern devices.

24.title: Rouge
24.description: Previewer page for J1 module Rouge. Rouge is a pure Ruby syntax highlighter. It can highlight over 100 different languages fully integrated with J1 Template.
